    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but some people say the whole structure is basically broken because the Security Council can just block everything whenever a big power is involved. do historians see those flaws as just part of how diplomacy works, or do they see the UN itself as kind of an outdated/failing system for the modern world?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
